  "source_id": "migraine",
  "name": "Migraine - Diagnosis Code Query (Multi-Subtype)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find migraine patients via diagnosis codes. Migraine is documented under multiple SNOMED codes by clinical subtype: parent migraine, migraine with aura, migraine without aura, hemiplegic migraine, and the broader headache disorder umbrella. Synthea distributes patients across these subtypes.",
  "prompt": "Find all patients diagnosed with migraine, including migraine with aura, migraine without aura, hemiplegic migraine, and headache disorders.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all patients with migraines.",
    "broad": "Find all patients diagnosed with any form of migraine \u2014 including the parent migraine concept, migraine with aura, migraine without aura, hemiplegic migraine, and the broader headache disorder umbrella.",
    "expert": "I need to identify all migraine patients. Migraine is documented under multiple SNOMED codes: Migraine (37796009) is the parent concept, with subtype-specific Migraine with aura (4473006), Migraine without aura (56097005), Hemiplegic migraine (59292006), and the broader umbrella Headache disorder (230461009). Search Condition resources for all five codes."
  },
